    "dynamic_rich_text_bNRBkf": {
      "type": "dynamic-rich-text",
      "name": "t:sections.rich_text.presets.rich_text.name",
      "settings": {
        "width": "full-width",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h2>Why LED lightbars outperform older warning lights</h2><p>LED light bars have replaced rotators and traditional strobes for good reason. They draw less current, run cooler, last tens of thousands of hours, and throw a sharper, brighter signal that cuts through daylight, rain, and fog alike. Today's bars layer in alley lights, takedown lights, and traffic-advisor functions, turning a single roof-mounted unit into a complete scene-management tool. If you're upgrading an older setup, switching to LED is the fastest way to boost conspicuity while cutting your amp draw — and it's the standard every professional agency now specs.</p><h2>Find the right lightbar for your vehicle</h2><p>No two jobs demand the same bar, so this collection is organized around exactly what your role requires. Match the housing size, mounting style, and output to the way you actually work:</p><ul><li>Need maximum presence on a highway shoulder?<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/full-size-lightbars\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Full-size light bars</span></a> deliver true 360-degree coverage with the highest lumen output and the widest feature sets.</li><li>Running a wrecker or recovery rig? Purpose-built<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/tow-lightbars\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">tow truck light bars</span></a> meet amber-warning expectations and mount cleanly on a cab or headache rack.</li><li>Working undercover or want a stealthier profile? Slim<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/interior-undercover-lightbars\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">interior and undercover lightbars</span></a> mount at the windshield or rear glass without giving your setup away.</li><li>Tight on roof space or budget?<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/mini-lightbars\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Compact mini light bars</span></a> pack surprising output into short housings, with magnetic or permanent mount options.</li></ul><p>Pair any bar with the right<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/strap-kits-parts-accessories\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">mounting straps and lightbar hardware</span></a> for a factory-clean install, or start with a complete<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/lightbar-packages\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">lightbar package</span></a> that bundles the bar, mounts, and controller together to save time and money.</p><h2>Trusted brands, guaranteed pricing</h2><p>This collection carries the names professionals ask for by name —<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/whelen-products\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Whelen light bars</span></a>, Feniex, Federal Signal, SoundOff Signal, and our own Strobes N' More line. That range lets you spec anything from a sub-$200 mini bar for a personal vehicle to a full Whelen Justice or Legacy build for a frontline patrol unit. And because we guarantee the best pricing on every lightbar we sell, if you find the same bar cheaper elsewhere, call us and we'll beat it.</p><h2>Built for how you actually work</h2><p>Choosing a light bar isn't only about brightness — color legality, mounting style, and control matter just as much. Amber bars are the standard for<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/public-works-construction\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">utility, construction, and towing fleets</span></a>, while red and blue are reserved for<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/law-enforcement\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">police vehicle lighting</span></a> and<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/fire-ems\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">ambulance and EMS units</span></a>. Many of our dual- and tri-color bars let one unit switch roles, which is ideal for agencies that share equipment across departments.</p><p>Round out the build with the supporting gear that makes a lightbar system work:<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/arrow-traffic-advisor-bars-1\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">traffic advisor bars</span></a> for directing traffic around a scene,<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/360-beacons-and-accessories\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">rotating beacons</span></a> for slow-moving equipment,<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/led-lights\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">surface-mount LED lights</span></a> for grille and perimeter coverage, and<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/sirens-speakers\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">sirens and speakers</span></a> plus<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/switches-controllers\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">control switches</span></a> to run it all from the cab. Prefer to leave the wiring to a pro? Our team offers<a href=\"https://strobesnmore.com/pages/installation-service\"> <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">professional installation and service</span></a> to get every light dialed in and DOT-compliant.</p><h2>Shop LED lightbars with confidence</h2><p>Every bar ships with the flash patterns, warranty, and support you'd expect from equipment people trust with their safety. Browse the full selection below, compare models side by side, and call our team at (401) 454-4487 if you'd like help matching a bar to your vehicle and application. When you need to be seen, don't settle; equip your rig with a lightbar built to do the job right the first time.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
        "text_alignment": "left"
      }
    },
